SIMPLE: piccolo
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Piccolo
<hw>Pic"co*lo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.,
small.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A small, shrill flute,
the pitch of which is an octave higher than the ordinary flute; an
octave flute.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A small upright piano.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An organ stop, with a high,
piercing tone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pice</ent>⟦br⟧
